!TITLE
DOWN, BUT NOT OUT
!WORDS
An old legend tells of an angel who was sent by God to inform Satan 
that all the methods he uses to defeat God's children would be taken 
from him. The devil pleaded to be allowed to keep just one. "Let me 
retain depression," he begged.  The angel, thinking this is a modest 
request, agreed. "Good!" he exclaimed, as he laughed to himself. "In 
that one gift, I have secured all."

     In his book Depression, What It Is and What to Do About It, 
Roger Barrett describes this condition as "a miserable, wretched 
experience that leaves you exhausted, uninvolved, and in deep, 
hopeless despair.  There seems to be absolutely nowhere to turn and 
not one single thing you can do to escape these horrible feelings.  
You feel doomed, trapped, and at the end of your rope....It's awful!"
!TOPICS
