!TITLE
A SURE HOPE
!WORDS
Some household pets become greatly disturbed by their owner's 
prolonged absence.  When temporarily placed in a boarding kennel, 
it's possible for them to have a heart attack.  Or they become so 
upset that they actually die from nervous exhaustion or from just 
giving up.  As a result, pet owners who are planning to leave their 
animals for a period of time are encouraged to give them "hope" by 
first helping them to "believe" that they will return.  This can be 
done by boarding the dog or cat for just a day or two once in a while 
to prepare it for longer absences.  These experiences teach the pet 
to expect its master to come back.  They can actually save its life.
!TOPICS
HOPE
LONELINESS
FAMILY
PETS
BELIEF
!SCRIPTURES
