!TITLE
THE POWER OF THE TONGUE
!WORDS
Leonard Greenway, commenting on the tongue, wrote, "There is an 
ancient fable about a monster known as Proteus who had the power of 
assuming many shapes and appearances.  He could become a tree or a 
pebble, a lion or a dove, a serpent or a lamb. He seemed to have 
little difficulty in passing from one form into another. That fabled 
creature reminds me of the human tongue.  It can bless or curse; it 
can express praise or whisper slander; it can speak a word of 
encouragement or spread the poison of vindictive hatred."
