!TITLE
LOVING IS DOING
!WORDS
In his book Mere Christianity, C. S. Lewis wrote, "Do not waste your 
time bothering whether you`love' your neighbor; act as if you did.  
As soon as we do this, we find one of the great secrets. When you are 
behaving as if you loved someone, you will presently come to love 
him.  If you injure someone you dislike, you will find yourself 
disliking him more.  If you do him a good turn, you will find 
yourself disliking him less."
