!TITLE
LOOKING UP AND LOOKING AHEAD
!WORDS
A Christian lady named Mrs. Bean said, "Every day I ask God to guide 
me and show me something I can do for Him."  And every day God 
answers her prayer.  Whether it's someone needing a warm, winning 
smile--and hers are priceless--a kind word of encouragement, or a 
listening ear, Mrs. Bean never lacks for opportunities to give of 
herself. Her wheelchair provides all the mobility she needs to keep 
reaching out to others.  She is 91 and has been in a nursing home for 
8 years.

   Another lady has the same spirit.  After commenting on her 
husband's long years as an architect and her own as a secretary, Mrs. 
Chenault wrote, "We feel sure that God has something more He wants us 
to do, and we are listening for what it may be, asking His guidance 
in what we are already doing."  Mr. and Mrs. Chenault are 92!
!TOPICS
