!TITLE
BEAUTY AIDS
!WORDS
Every year millions of dollars are spent on beauty aids to preserve 
or restore the fresh, supple look of youth.  According to the ads, 
even "unsightly age spots" and "tiny crow's feet" will yield to the 
amazing restorative powers of these precious emollients.  But let's 
face it, all they do is delay the inevitable.

     It is said that one of President Lincoln's advisors recommended 
a certain man for his cabinet, but Lincoln turned him down.  When the 
aide asked why, the President replied, "I don't like his face."  "But 
the poor fellow isn't responsible for his face," said the advisor. 
"Every man over 40 is responsible for his face," Lincoln responded.
