!TITLE
THE PARABLE OF THE THIMBLE
!WORDS
When we read about the population explosion, do we consider what it 
means as far as the cause of Christ is concerned? Missionaries both 
at home and abroad have found it absolutely impossible to keep up 
with the rapidly expanding harvest field of the world.  Every day 
there are more and more people and comparatively fewer Christians.  
We cannot begin to put a dent in the tremendous task that awaits us 
until each believing layman gets busy for the Lord and starts working 
and witnessing for Christ.  The laborers are too few!

     Recently when a wife saw her husband trying to sew on a button, 
she told him the thimble was on the wrong finger. "I know," he said, 
"it should be on yours!"  This amusing little story makes a point 
that is worth our consideration.  Too often we are critical of others 
who are active in some particular work for the Savior just because 
they don't handle it the way we think it should be done.  How much 
better to put the "thimble on our own finger" and start bearing the 
responsibility the Lord has given us as His children.  It's easy to 
sit on the sidelines and criticize, but it's something else to get on 
the team and start doing our part.  The apostle Paul warns us that 
"every man shall receive his own reward according to his own labor" 
(1 Cor. 3:8).
!TOPICS
MISSIONS
HARVEST
CRITICISM
LABORERS
POPULATION EXPLOSION
RESPONSIBILITY, CHRISTIAN
TEAMWORK
REWARD
!SCRIPTURES
1 CORINTHIANS 3:3-10
LUKE 10:2
ISAIAH 56:10
JEREMIAH 3:15
EZEKIEL 34:2
JOHN 4:37
1 THESSALONIANS 5:12
2 TIMOTHY 2:4
