!TITLE
CONSCIENCE AND THE BIBLE
!WORDS
A Christian father and his young daughter were out driving and had to 
stop for a traffic signal.  The daughter made a remark which gave the 
father an opportunity to teach her a valuable lesson about 
conscience.  He has summarized it in these poetic lines:

  'It was well you stopped
     When the red light flashed,'
  She said as we drove along;
     For an officer stood at the corner there,
  In charge of the traffic throng.
     And I smiled and said to my daughter fair,
  As we waited on the spot,
     'I always stop when the red light shows,
  Be an officer there or not.'
     Then she sat and thought as we drove along,
  And suddenly this she said,
     'There ought to be lights
  For us all through life,
     The amber and green and red.
  What a help 'twould be if a red light flashed
     When danger and shame were near,
  And we all might wait till the green light came
     To show that the road was clear.'
 'Well, my dear,' said I, 'we have tried to light
     Life's road for your feet to fare,
 And we pray you'll stop when the red light glows,
     For none of us may be there.
 We've tried to teach you what God says is wrong
     And the way to live serene;
 So stop when your conscience shows up red
     And go when it flashes green.'"
!TOPICS
CONSCIENCE
OBEDIENCE
TRAINING
CHOICES, MORAL
WARNINGS
