!TITLE
MAKING THE MOST OF LIFE
!WORDS
A life-threatening experience has a way of rearranging our 
priorities.  That has been true in the lives of former Texas Governor 
John Connally and his wife for more than 25 years.  Mr. Connally was 
wounded by the assassin who took the life of President John F. 
Kennedy in 1963.  He notes that the experience profoundly changed 
their lives. In a newspaper interview, Connally explained, "As far as 
Nellie and I are concerned, I think the more lasting impression it 
made on us was that it inevitably brought into sharper focus what's 
really important in life.  And we have since that time tried to act 
and conduct ourselves in a way [that] we don't engage in much trivia, 
and we try not to participate in things that are shallow or in the 
long run meaningless."
!TOPICS
PRIORITIES
LIFE, BREVITY OF
SUFFERING
