!TITLE
SPIRITUAL SIT-ITUS
!WORDS
A leading life insurance company recently published an interesting 
article entitled "Sit-itus."  It reads in part:  "There is a deadly 
malady from which many Americans are rapidly dying between the neck 
and the waistline.  It deteriorates the heart, lungs, kidneys, and 
liver; and it develops as the result of sitting at home, riding in an 
automobile, or engaging in the same type of sendentary practices at 
work."
     In the church, sit-itus is hav habits?"  The minister was silent 
until they met a man who was especially unkempt and filthy.  His hair 
was hanging down his neck, and he had half an inch of stubble on his 
face.  The preacher was ready with his response: "You can't be a very 
good barber or you wouldn't permit a man like that to continue living 
in this neighborhood without a haircut and a shave." Indignantly the 
atheist answered, "Why blame me for that man's condition?  I can't 
help it if he's like that.  He has never given me a chance!  If he 
would only come to my shop, I could fix him up and make him look like 
a gentleman!" Giving the barber a penetrating look, the minister 
said, "Then don't blame God for allowing these people to continue in 
their evil ways when He graciously invites them to come to Him and be 
saved. They are slaves to sin and evil habits because they refuse to 
accept the One who died to save and deliver them."
