!TITLE
THE CAPE OF GOOD HOPE!
!WORDS
At the southern tip of Africa a cape jutting out into the ocean used 
to cause sailors great anxiety and struggle.  Many who attempted to 
said around it were lost in the swirling seas. Since adverse weather 
conditions often prevailed there, the region was named the Cape of 
Storms.  A Portuguese captain determined to find a safe route through 
those waters so that his countrymen could reach Cathay and obtain the 
riches of the East Indies. He succeeded in his difficult task, and 
the area was renamed the Cape of Good Hope

     We all are faced with that last great storm called death. But 
our blessed Lord has traveled through that maelstrom, and He tells us 
there is light and a bright treasure beyond.  Through His offering on 
the cross and His victorious resurrection, He has quelled our fears 
and opened the way to Heaven.  Now all who know Him as Savior can 
face life's final voyage, not as the cape of storms but as the cape 
of good hope!
!TOPICS
