!TITLE
ORDINARY PEOPLE
!WORDS
In A.D. 391, an obscure hermit who was deeply disturbed by the horror 
of the gladiatorial games decided to do something about it.  So one 
day he joined 80,000 spectators in the stands. Suddenly he left his 
seat, ran into the arena, and stepped between the fighters.  The 
onlookers roared their disapproval, a command rang out, and he was 
killed on the spot.  But his death was not in vain.  When the word 
spread that he was a devout man of God, and that he was protesting 
this cruel sport, a hush fell over the huge stadium and many felt a 
deep sense of shame.  That was the last gladiator contest in the 
Roman Empire.

     Don't think that only gifted or well-known personalities can 
make a great impact for God. The Lord blesses the efforts of common 
folks who are faithful in serving Him.  Any believer can witness to a 
neighbor, pray for a missionary, or show kindness to the needy.  The 
saving of just one person has eternal consequences, for he in turn 
may win many others to the Savior.
!TOPICS
COURAGE, OF CONVICTIONS
TESTIMONY
SALT, OF THE EARTH
PROTEST, EFFECTS OF
!SCRIPTURES
