!TITLE
DISPLACED PERSONS
!WORDS
During World War II many civilians in battle-torn countries could be 
seen with the identifying initials DP on their clothing, which stood 
for "displaced persons."  Most of these people were relocated in 
other countries.  Some of them quickly adopted the ways of their new 
homeland, and soon their distinct national traits were lost.  Others, 
however, refused to be swallowed up by a different culture.  You 
could always tell they were from another country because they 
retained their own language and customs.

    This should also be true of us as Christians, for in a spiritual 
sense we too are displaced persons.  Our "citizenship is in heaven," 
and we are "pilgrims and strangers" here on earth.
!TOPICS
SOJOURNERS
WWII, DISPLACED PERSONS FROM
