!TITLE
HIS LOVE NEVER FAILS
!WORDS
When the Civil War broke out, a young man who was engaged to a 
beautiful girl from New England was one of the first to be called 
into service.  Their marriage therefore had to be postponed.  The 
young solider managed to come through most of the conflict uninjured, 
but finally in the Battle of the Wilderness he was severely wounded.  
The lady he loved, not knowing of his condition, was counting the 
days until he would return.  She waited eagerly for word from him, 
but no more letters came.  At last she received an envelope addressed 
in unfamiliar handwriting.  Opening it, she read the words, "It is 
very difficult for me to tell you this, but I have lost both my 
arms!  I cannot write myself, so a friend is doing it for me. You are 
as dear to me as ever, but I will be dependent upon others for the 
rest of my life. Therefore I feel I should release you from the 
obligation of our engagement."  

Immediately the young woman took the next train and went directly to 
the hospital where her finance was confined. Tearfully she walked 
past row after row of wounded men, looking for her lover.  The moment 
her eyes fell upon him, she threw her arms around his neck and kissed 
him.  "I will never give up!" she cried. "My hands will help you.  I 
am able to support you.  I will take care of you!"  Her unwavering 
devotion solved the young soldier's problem and brought him great joy 
and security.
!TOPICS
LOVE, TRUE
CIVIL WAR, WOUNDED IN
AMPUTATION, OF ARMS
DECOTION, TO WOULDED
!SCRIPTURES
