!TITLE
WHAT HE HAS GIVEN THEE
!WORDS
The Hebrew word for "burden" in Psalm 55:22 is used only once in the 
entire Old Testament.  It literally means, "what he has given thee." 
Sometimes because of needless worry we take unnecessary cares upon 
ourselves.

     A believer who had many problems dreamed he saw a multitude of 
people weighed down with various burdens.  All of them were 
Christians, yet each was staggering beneath a heavy load.  He was 
amazed to see that from time to time the Lord Himself was permitting 
their oppression to increase.  Still the weary ones went on, although 
there were almost ready to drop in their tracks from exhaustion.  
Then, to add to their grief, even more afflictions were piled upon 
them. Greatly perplexed, the dreamer finally approached the Lord and 
humbly inquired why He allowed all of this to happen.  The Savior 
replied, "I'm letting their distress build up until they can no 
longer do without my help.  Then as they turn to Me in desperation, 
I'll carry both them and their burdens.
