!TITLE
THE BLESSINGS OF AFFLICTION
!WORDS
The psalmist tells us that before he encountered trials and 
difficulties, he would stray from the path of God's choosing. But 
after he suffered affliction, he learned to look to the Lord for 
direction.

    During the Second World War metallurgists tested the steel being 
used to build tanks for American soldiers in the front lines.  They 
had to be sure that the metal was not too hard or too soft as it 
passed through the tempering furnaces. Tension was applied to 
ascertain its breaking point.   Checks were also taken to make 
certain that the armor would be bulletproof.  If any flaws showed up 
in the steel, it would undergo more tempering.  When it left the 
factory, it was fully prepared to withstand the stress demanded of it.

    So it is with God's children.  To make us fit for His work and 
the instruments of His praise, He puts us through the kiln of trial 
and places us in the testing room of life.  Pressures are constantly 
applied to sanctify us and to reveal the weaknesses which only His 
grace can remedy.
