!TITLE
IT CAME TO PASS
!WORDS
While a missionary was conducting a meeting in a village, he asked 
some Christians to share their favorite Scripture passages with the 
group.  A number of verses were quoted, most of them on salvation, 
assurance, or God's provision.  One elderly man, however, stood to 
his feet and said that his favorite words in the Bible were, "It came 
to pass."  He continued, "When sickness strikes, it encourages me to 
know that it will pass.  When I find myself in trouble, I know it 
won't last forever.  I'll soon be able to say, "It came to pass.'"

    Now, this man had placed a different meaning on those words than 
the writers of Scripture intended.  But to his way of thinking, they 
suggested an important truth.  No matter how unending a trial may 
seem, the day will come when it will no longer be a burden or a 
source of distress.  In fact, it will seem like nothing in the light 
of eternity.
!TOPICS
TRIALS, PASSING OF
PATIENCE, NEED FOR
ENDURANCE
AGE, WISDOM OF
WISDOM, OF AGE
