!TITLE
WHY DO I GO TO CHURCH?
!WORDS
Before we are too harsh in judging these scribes and Pharisees of 
Jesus's day, let's stop and look at ourselves.  All too many 
Christians today go to church to find fault, to gossip, and to 
criticize. Warren Wiersbe, in his book Angry People, wrote, "An 
incident in the life of Joseph Parker, the great British preacher, 
illustrates this tragic truth.  He was preaching at the City Temple 
in London.  After the service one of the listeners came up to him and 
said, 'Dr. Parker, you made a grammatical error in your sermon.'  He 
then proceeded to point out the error to the pastor. Joseph Parker 
looked at the man and said, 'And what else did you get out of the 
message?'  What a fitting rebuke!"

   No one in the church is perfect - not the pastor, the organist, 
the song leader, or the ushers.  We all make mistakes.
