!TITLE
THE SHELTERING HAND
!WORDS
In one of the art galleries of Europe is a painting that may cause 
the casual observer to be somewhat puzzled.  It portrays a solitary 
figure, bowed down with fear or grief, running across a bleak and 
barren landscape.  Overhead hangs an ominous cloud. At first glance 
you might wonder about the artist's purpose and what message he was 
trying to convey.  But upon closer inspection you notice that the 
cloud has the shape of a great hand.  Suddenly the meaning of the 
picture becomes clear. That lonely, frightened traveler, seeking 
refuge from a bursting storm, is actually under the protecting care 
of God's infinite power and love.

  So it is with every believer in the Lord Jesus. The blackest shadow 
of life's trials is but the wise providence of our God sheltering us 
from the burning sun.  Or it may be intended to get us to flee 
Christ who is a perfect shelter in any storm.
!TOPICS
FEAR
GRIEF
CARE, GOD
REFUGE, GOD OUR
