!TITLE
I NEVER LOOKED UP FROM HERE
!WORDS
A man named Mark was on a golf course he had played many times 
before.  Suddenly he exclaimed to his golfing partners, "Look at that 
beautiful sight!"  There, stretching away over the golden sand dunes, 
was a marvelous view of Lake Michigan, its sparkling blue waters 
shimmering in summer splendor.  Always before on that particular 
hole, Mark had been concerned with a golfing problem--the chip he had 
to make or the putt he had to sink. His eyes had always been focused 
downward.  "I never looked up from here before!" he exclaimed.

  Mark was somewhat life the people to whom Isaiah was speaking with 
prophetic foreview (Isa. 40:26). They would be in exile in Babylon, 
with their homeland far away and their situation precarious. The 
prophet urged them to look up, to lift their eyes on high and 
remember the majesty and power and faithfulness of the Sovereign Lord.
!TOPICS
PERSPECTIVE
VISION
GOLF
