!TITLE
TIME BOMBS
!WORDS
In one of their books on the Watergate affair entitled Final Days, 
Robert Woodward and Carl Bernstein included a paragraph that to me 
illustrated the truth of Proverbs 28:13. They wrote:  "In defending 
himself, the President had planted time bombs....Nixon had concealed, 
he had hedged, he had lied.  Some of the bombs had already gone off, 
and the rest lay ticking." As we now know, they did go off, resulting 
in the President's resignation.

  When sins are unconfessed and covered up, they truly are like time 
bombs.  They cannot stay hidden forever.  Consider Achan, whose story 
we read today.  Disobeying the command of the Lord to destroy 
everything in Jericho, he kept a garment, a wedge of gold, and some 
silver.  When he buried the treasure in his tent, however, he did not 
dream that it was like planting a time bomb. But there the hidden 
objects lay, "ticking," until Israel's shameful defeat at Ai.  Then 
Achan's sin was exposed, and he was punished.
!TOPICS
CONFESSION
HIDDEN SINS
LYING
WATERGATE
NIXON, RICHARD
ACHAN
DECEPTION
!SCRIPTURES
