!TITLE
COURAGE IN THE MIDST OF FEAR
!WORDS
Courage is not the absence of fear.  Someone has said, "Courage is 
fear that has said its prayers." Being a Christian neither guarantees 
fortitude nor frees us of all anxious feelings.  It does give us 
God's Word, however, which when appropriated by faith makes dread and 
apprehension lose their paralyzing power.

  Well-known pianist and composer Don Wyrtzen sits at the keyboard 
before large audiences with poise and confidence.  But he candidly 
admits to becoming anxious at times.  "I can even have an anxiety 
attack," says Don.  "What I do may sound simplistic, but it really 
works.  I just sing quietly to myself verses like, 'Thou wilt keep 
him in perfect peace whose mind is stayed on Thee.' I'm not saying 
that instantly the Lords waves a magic wand and the anxiety goes 
away, but I have experienced complete serenity from God in a time 
when I am anxious."
