!TITLE
QUIET PLEASE
!WORDS
For the last 3 years an architectural firm in Denver, Colorado, has 
had a "quiet time" for its employees.  Sixty minutes of silence are 
set aside each day at midmorning for thinking and planning. It has 
proven to be an essential feature for the staff of 25 who work 
together in one large open room.  One employee said that at first the 
idea didn't sound very good to them.  But now, having discovered its 
benefits, they have become very protective of their quiet time.  They 
have found it to be an important aid in realizing one of the firm's 
goals, which is to have an atmosphere of "integrity and calmness."

  Daniel is a good example of someone who achieved on a personal 
level a calmness and integrity that made his life effective for God.  
He successfully countered the strain of his demanding activities by a 
regular habit of being quiet before the Lord three times a day.  
There was a direct relationship between Daniel's habit of prayer and 
the personal courage, uncompromising character, and spiritual power 
that marked his life.  It was during these quiet times that he 
acknowledged his dependence on the Lord and asked Him for help--help 
that would deliver him alive out of the lions' den.
!TOPICS
QUIET TIME
DAILY DEVOTIONS
