!TITLE
MOVE ONLY FORWARD
!WORDS
The Christian life must be marked by growth.  We will not grow if we 
return to those things that marked our past life.  We must keep 
moving forward.

  The Australian coat of arms pictures two creatures, an emu (a large 
bird that cannot fly) and a kangaroo.  They were chosen by the 
Australians for this honor because of one common 
characteristic--neither can move backward.  If an emu, with its big, 
three-toed feet, tries to go backward, it will fall over. And the 
kangaroo is kept from going backward by its long tail. As a result, 
they can only go forward, thus portraying the spirit of Australia.

  As believers in Christ, we should resolve to keep making spiritual 
strides forward in specific areas of our lives.
!TOPICS
SPIRITUAL GROWTH
PROGRESS, SPIRITUAL
FORWARD
KANGAROO
