!TITLE
THE GIFT BEHIND THE GIFT
!WORDS
When the 9-year-old grandson asked his grandfather what he should get 
Grandma for her birthday, Grandpa kiddingly told him,  "A mink coat 
or a Mercedes."  The boy grinned and said he had only about $5.00.  
Grandpa then assured him that she would be happier with a small gift 
from him than she would be with a mink coat from someone she didn't 
know.  Just the fact that he cared enough to select a present for her 
would please her more than the gift itself.

  Paul deeply appreciated the generosity of the Phillipian 
believers.  He knew that the Lord would care for his needs, but he 
was touched that they wanted to be God's instrument in meeting those 
needs.
