!TITLE
THE END OF TEARS
!WORDS
An elderly Christian lady lay dying.  Her beloved husband sat by her 
bedside tenderly holding her hand.  They both knew that the end was 
near and that they soon would be parted.  As their eyes met, a tear 
flowed down the old woman's wrinkled cheek. Gently, her husband wiped 
it away.  Then, with a quaver in his voice, he said, "Thank God, 
Mary, that's the last!"

  When ties of love are broken, tears flow freely, and this is as it 
should be.  But for the one who is going to heaven, as well as for us 
who remain, the parting is not final.  Our hearts rest in the 
assurance that one day separation and tears will give way to unending 
joy.
!TOPICS
