!TITLE
RESTING ON THE PROMISES
!WORDS
Old Uncle Oscar took his first airplane ride. Knowing that he had 
been somewhat apprehensive about it, his friends were eager to hear 
how it went.  At the first opportunity, they asked him if he enjoyed 
the flight.  "Well," commented Uncle Oscar, "it wasn't as bad as I 
thought it might be. But I'll tell you this.  I never did put all my 
weight down!"

  That's how some Christians take the promises of the Bible. They 
have no trouble believing what is says about the Lord Jesus Christ 
saving all who place their trust in Him.  They know their sins have 
been forgiven and that heaven is their eternal home.  But they fail 
to take the Lord at His word when it applies to other areas of their 
lives.  They've never "put all their weight down." As a result they 
are plagued by doubts, fears, and uncertainties.
!TOPICS
