!TITLE
HOW'S YOUR APPETITE?
!WORDS
In a letter to a relative, a lady in a nursing home wrote, "I have 
every comfort I could wish for.  My meals are the best, and they're 
cooked just right.  My friends send me baskets of the finest fruit.  
But I can hardly force myself to eat. I've no appetite and I'm 
gradually losing weight."  The poor woman had completely lost her 
desire for any kind of food.

  A similar condition exists in the lives of many backslidden 
Christians.  Their taste for the Word of God is gone.  The healthy 
believer, however realizes that the Bible is food for the soul.
