!TITLE
DEAD END?
!WORDS
A pastor and his wife were driving through the country on a muggy 
Sunday afternoon.  Haze filled the air.  Rain was imminent.  All at 
once they came upon a miniature metropolis of granite gravestones.  
It was a typical old country cemetery. But this particular graveyard 
had one striking feature. Bordering one side was a gravel road, and 
on the corner this sign:  DEAD END.

  What a graphic reminder of how some people view life!  Their 
existence on this planet is a brief drive through time that leads to 
a dead end.  To them, death ends all.
  Yet if that is true, then Jesus was either ignorant or deceitful.
!TOPICS
