!TITLE
THE SHEPHERD'S VOICE
!WORDS
 A man in Australia was arrested and charged with stealing a sheep.  
But he claimed emphatically that it was one of his own that had been 
missing for many days.  When the case went to court, the judge was 
puzzled, not knowing how to decide the matter.  At last he asked that 
the sheep be brought into the courtroom.  Then he ordered the 
plaintiff to step outside and call the animal. The sheep made no 
response except to raise its head and look frightened.
  The judge then instructed the defendant to go to the courtyard and 
call the sheep.  When the accused man began to make his distinctive 
call, the sheep bounded toward the door.  It was obvious that he 
recognized the familiar voice of his master. "His sheep know him," 
said the judge. "Case dismissed!"
!TOPICS
SHEPHERD, CHRIST OUR
LOYALTY TO CHRIST
KNOWING CHRIST
