!TITLE
THE LAW AND THE SWAMP
!WORDS
 The Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) ordered the cleanup of 
wastewater emptying into the Great Swamp National Wildlife Refuge in 
New Jersey.  To comply with the law, one township built a new water 
treatment plant.  The newer and larger plant, however, now dumps much 
more water into the 6,000-acre swamp, threatening the balance of 
nature.  Flooding has increased and wildlife is being destroyed.  
Unless something is done, the swamp will eventually be ruined.  A 
good law that was intended to preserve life has ended up destroying 
life.

  God's law is also good.  Its high standards of purity point out our 
sin and require justice.  It condemns our polluted ways and demands 
that we obey God's regulations.  But without God's mercy, His law 
would drown us in its rightness.

  Only Christ can demand moral cleanness without destroying us in the 
process.  Only Christ, in His grace, works in us to produce a pure 
heart, a good conscience, and a sincere faith. Only Christ can clean 
up the guilt of our sin, promote clean living, and preserve us 
blameless in the day of the Lord Jesus Christ.
!TOPICS
LAW, GOD'S
GRACE, GOD'S
STANDARDS
MORALS
PURITY, MORAL
HOLINESS OF LIFE
MERCY, GOD'S
PERFECTION
ENVIRONMENT
!SCRIPTURES
