!TITLE
WHO GETS THE LOVE?
!WORDS
 A sociologist was writing a book about the difficulties of growing 
up in a large family, so he interviewed the mother of 13 children.  
After several basic questions, he asked, "Do you think all children 
deserve the full, impartial love and attention of a mother?"

    "Of course," said the mother.

    "Well, which of your children do you love the most?" he asked, 
hoping to catch her in a contradiction.
   She answered, "The one who is sick until he gets well, and the one 
who is away until he gets home."
   That mother's response is like the shepherd who left 99 sheep to 
seek the one that was lost, the woman who searched for the one coin 
and the father who threw a party when his wayward son returned.
!TOPICS
LOVE, GOD'S
SHEPHERD, CHRIST OUR
MOTHERS
FAMILIES, LARGE
