!TITLE
IN HARM'S WAY
!WORDS
 A construction crew was building a new road through a rural area, 
knocking down trees as it progressed.  A superintendent noticed that 
one tree had a nest of birds who couldn't yet fly. He marked the tree 
so that it wouldn't be cut down.

   Several weeks later the superintendent came to the tree.  He got 
into a bucket truck and was lifted up so that he could peer into the 
nest. The fledglings were gone.  They had obviously learned to fly.  
The superintendent ordered the tree cut down.

   As the tree crashed to the ground, the nest fell clear, and some 
of the material that the birds had gathered to make the nest was 
scattered about.  Part of it was a scrap torn from a Sunday school 
pamphlet.  On the little strip of paper were these words:  "He careth 
for you."

    [Bits & Pieces, Vol. M, No 1D.  Page 10.]
!TOPICS
