!TITLE
IN THE STORMS OF LIFE
!WORDS
 A train was overtaken by a great storm.  All the passengers were 
greatly afraid as they saw the lightning and heard the thunder. In 
one seat, however, was a little fellow who seemed to be totally 
undisturbed as he sat playing with his toys. One of the passengers 
turned to him and said, "Son, I see that you are all alone on this 
train.  Aren't you afraid to travel alone and in such a storm?"  The 
child lifted his head and answered, "No, sir, I am not afraid at all 
because my father is the conductor of this train.

   The storms of this world may indeed disturb us, but that 
disturbance is dissipated when we realize that it is all in God's 
hands.  Of course, it makes a difference if we have made God our 
Father through receiving Christ as our personal Savior.

   [Pulpit Helps, Nov 1992.  Page 14.]
