!TITLE
POW!
!WORDS
 In a Peanuts cartoon, Charlie Brown winds up on the pitcher;s mound, 
and with self-confidence quotes Scripture:  "Thou shalt not be afraid 
of the terror by night, nor of the pestilence that walketh in 
darkness..."

   In the next frame, WHAM! the ball comes zooming back from the 
batter, catapulting Charlie head over heels.  Then in the last frame 
we see him lying face down on the ground with stars dancing around 
his head.  He concludes, "But those line drives will kill you!"
