!TITLE
TENSION BREAKER
!WORDS
 Tivoli Gardens, a famous amusement area in Copenhagen, Denmark, has 
a very unusual attraction.  For a small charge, customers can try to 
shatter pieces of chinaware by hitting them with small wooden balls.  
Flawed products from area manufacturers are hung on racks at the end 
of the gallery, and each participant gets five chances to smash the 
plates, cups, saucers, and other items of china into smithereens.  
Touted as a great tension breaker, the activity is supposed to rid 
the person of unwanted anxiety.

   Breaking china may be fun and may soothe frayed nerves, but 
Christians have a better means of experiencing relief from tension 
and worry.  We can find release from anxiety when we remember that we 
are always under God's watchful eye and trust Him for His protection 
and provision.
!TOPICS
