!TITLE
MORAL CONVICTIONS
!WORDS
 Moral character is developed when we take the Bible seriously. Its 
strength is revealed when it costs us something to stand up for truth.

   Elizabeth Skoglund writes that during World War II, when housing 
in Chicago was scarce, her father inquired about renting an apartment 
from a Swedish woman.  When she quoted an outlandish amount for the 
rent, he was shocked.  But then he remembered an earlier comment she 
had made, and he suspected that she thought he was a Jew.  So he 
began talking to her fluently in Swedish, and she cut the rent in 
half.  "No thank you,"  said Skoglund's father as he turned to 
leave.  "Nothing you could say and no rent reduction you could offer 
could make me live here now."
