!TITLE
UNLIMITED POWER
!WORDS
 David Branon tells about the time he and his family were savoring 
the last few minutes of their vacation at a campground: "The usual 
mode of transportation at the park is a golf cart, and we were taking 
out last swing around the lake before going back to the trailer and 
heading home.  But we didn't make it. About halfway around the lake 
our battery-powered cart stopped dead in its tracks.  It had run out 
of energy.  It was a long push back.

    "A golf cart has no power of its own.  Every ounce of energy our 
cart used to haul us around came from an outside source. Each night 
we plugged the buggy in to an electrical outlet that juiced it up for 
the next day.  The problem on our last excursion was that we had 
driven too far.

    "We do the same thing in our spiritual life all the time.  We 
forget that our power is 'of God and not of us', and that we need out 
spiritual batteries recharged every day.  Instead, we keep going on 
our own until we run out of energy and nothing is left with which to 
serve the Lord.
!TOPICS
POWER, SPIRITUAL
ENERGY, SPIRITUAL
BURNOUT
HOLY SPIRIT
RENEWAL
STRENGTH, GOD'S
