!TITLE
LOVE IS AN ACTIVE VERB
!WORDS
 A young man had been seriously injured in an automobile accident.  
As he recuperated, he was more and more impressed with the sterling 
qualities he saw in the orthopedist who cared for him.  This man, 
though pressed for time, was patient and kind with everyone.  He 
often went far beyond the call of duty, returning to the hospital 
during the night just to check on a critical patient.

   After the man had recovered, he went to the doctor's office for a 
checkup.  Looking at the physician with genuine curiosity, he said, 
"Doctor, what makes you tick?  Because, whatever it is, I've decided 
that I want it."  The orthopedist replied, "I'm a Christian," and he 
went on to tell about his conversion to Christ. The patient saw 
Christian love in the life of that surgeon and became a believer.
