!TITLE
THE KEY TO CERTAINTY
!WORDS
 When the famous biologist Louis Pasteur stood at the bedside of his 
dying daughter, he said, "I know only scientifically determined 
truth, but I am going to believe what I wish to believe, what I 
cannot help but believe--I expect to meet this child in another 
world."

   Pasteur's great affirmation of faith stopped short of being 
absolute scientific certainty.  The most devoted and knowledgeable 
Christian scholars today agree that our religious claims cannot be 
subjected to laboratory testing and proven scientifically.  Yet 
Pasteur was right.

   Our certainty comes from God as He helps us to sense in our hearts 
the reality of His love for us.  That inner witness is as sure as any 
scientific test.  Jesus said that all who love Him will be assured of 
His love and the Father's.
!TOPICS
ASSURANCE
FAITH
DOUBT
SCIENCE
TRUTH
CERTAINTY
