!TITLE
DEATH SENTENCE
!WORDS
 Ann Jillian was filled with terror when she discovered an 
irregularity in her breast.  She immediately imagined the worst. 
Cancer!  She stopped by her church, numb and alarmed, on her way to 
her appointment with the doctor.  She saw these word by St. Francis 
de Sales inscribed above the entrance:

    "The same everlasting Father who cares for you today will take 
care of you tomorrow and every day.  Either He will shield you from 
suffering, or He will give you the strength to bear it. Be at peace, 
then, and put aside all anxious thoughts and imaginations."

   Those words, which she had never noticed before, helped her 
tremendously.  "Up to that point," she said, "everything was 
turbulent.  Now I released everything into God's hands. Of course, 
God wants to help me."
