!TITLE
IT ONLY TAKES A SPARK
!WORDS
 Byron Paulus writes, "I wonder how Jeremiah Lanphier felt when he 
posted a notice on the door of the North Dutch Reformed Church on 
Fulton Street in New York City in 1857.  Prayer seemed to be the 
furthest thing from the mind of a nation caught up in the greed and 
secularism fostered by the Industrial Revolution. Then, when only six 
people showed up at that first prayer meeting, how easily, Lanphier 
could have despaired.  But thank God, he persevered, little 
suspecting that God was preparing to send the entire nation to its 
knees!

    "By human standards, Jeremiah Lanphier was not an extraordinary 
man--we don't even know when he died or where he was buried.  But he 
understood the necessity of prayer.  And God used him as a spark to 
launch the great Prayer Revival of 1858, in the wake of which over a 
million people were born into the Kingdom."

   [Life Action Ministries Revival Report, Apr 1993.  Page 3.]
