!TITLE
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
!WORDS
 What are you doing to stay healthy?  The question is not what do you 
know about good health. There's a big difference.  That's a point Dr. 
Neil Solomon made in his newspaper column.  He wrote,  "So you'd like 
to stay healthy--most people would. Fine, what are you doing about 
it?"  He concluded, "I've always been puzzled that so many people 
take better care of their cars than they do of themselves."

   Let's apply this to another area of life.  What are we doing to 
stay spiritually healthy?  The question is not what we know about 
staying spiritually healthy.  Most of us are well-versed on that 
subject.  We're familiar with what our Lord said about being poor in 
spirit, mournful over sin, meek, hungry and thirsty for 
righteousness, merciful, pure in heart, peacemakers, and persecuted 
for righteousness' sake.  Most of us know those laws of spiritual 
health, but what are we doing about them?
!TOPICS
HEALTH, SPIRITUAL
SPIRITUAL GROWTH
KNOWLEDGE
SCRIPTURE, APPLYING
CHRISTIAN LIFE
GROWTH, SPIRITUAL
