!TITLE
OUR PATIENT GOD
!WORDS
 It's amazing how patient Nathan's mom is with him. He's three years 
old, and he's all boy.  He can't stand the sight of a picked-up, 
freshly vacuumed room, so he delights in dumping toys all over the 
floor, though he has no intention of playing with them.  If he's 
upstairs and Mom's downstairs on the phone, he demands her attention 
at full volume.

   When Nathan wants comfort, he expects her to stop everything and 
hold him.  And about the time Mom's ready to "trade him in," his blue 
eyes and smile melt it all away.

   Yes, it takes patience to parent three-year- olds.  They forget.  
They choose to disobey.  They create havoc with their surroundings 
and with our emotions.

   Come to think of it, our heavenly Father would probably say that 
some of His spiritual children-- people like you and me--can be 
guilty of pretty exasperating behavior.  We're slow to learn.  We 
have setbacks.  We choose to break the rules. We create havoc with 
things we say and do.  We're so fragile and so demanding.

   Yet our heavenly Father parents us with love and compassion and 
tenderness.
!TOPICS
PATIENCE, GOD'S
FATHER, GOD OUR
CHILDREN
FRUSTRATION
EXASPERATION
SPIRITUAL GROWTH
GROWTH, SPIRITUAL
IMMATURITY, SPIRITUAL
