!TITLE
BREAKING DOWN BARRIERS
!WORDS
 Bob Boyd writes: "Many people have built-in barriers to hearing the 
gospel which can be broken only by love.
    "Ray was a tough high school senior who had drifted far from 
God.  At 3:00 one morning, he stumbled home drunk.  Through the 
heating vents of the house he heard the sobs of his mother as she 
prayed for him.  What he heard made him more determined to have 
nothing to do with her 'religion.'
    "One day Ray's mother pleaded with him to hear the visiting 
evangelist at her church.  Ray shouted, 'Look, if you'll shut up, 
I'll go to one meeting!'  Immediately she turned on her heel and 
walked away.  All week she said nothing to Ray. The final evening Ray 
walked into the kitchen two hours before the meeting and found his 
supper with a note from his mom.
    "'Why did she leave early?' he asked his dad.
    "'She didn't want to risk talking with you.'
    "'Well, I'm not going to any...'
    "Ray's dad cut in: 'I've never seen your mother so quiet about 
anything that she believes in.  You promised to go to that service 
tonight, and you are going, even if I have to drag you there myself!'
    "Ray decided that he had better go.  That night at the church he 
realized for the first time that God is real.  Ray asked Jesus Christ 
into his life.  At first he felt nothing.  Then he sensed an inner 
voice saying, 'Your sins are forgiven.' Suddenly the weight of the 
years lifted from Ray's shoulders.  His life was changed, and today 
he is a pastor."
   [Decision, Apr 1994.  Page 29.]
!TOPICS
LOVE FOR OTHERS
WITNESSING
EVANGELISM
MOTHERS
PRAYER, ANSWERED
QUIET SPIRIT
!SCRIPTURES
