!TITLE
OPEN MY EYES
!WORDS
Jean Coty writes:  "The pitcher was handed down to me through my 
father.  It sat in plain view all my growing up years--a pottery jug 
with dark brown glazed finish, a white hunting scene painted around 
its fat middle, and a sort of twisted handle. In those years we used 
it every night for pouring tea.  Later in my adult life, I continued 
to use if often because the feel of it in my hand called up instant 
memories of home

    "A few years ago I attended a lecture on ceramics.  The speaker 
told of English hunt jugs with handles shaped like sleek hunting 
dogs.  When I returned home, I took the old pitcher out of the 
cupboard for a closer look, and sure enough, the handle I always 
thought was merely twisted had the shape of a hunting hound standing 
on its hind legs.  I blinked and looked again.  The hound was there 
as clear as day.  I could not believe that I had overlooked something 
so obvious on the familiar old jug, but my newly opened eyes now saw 
the truth.

    "God has put wonderful things in His Word for us, but we often 
approach Scripture with eyes closed by preset ideas, cluttered minds, 
unbelief, or sin.  God will reveal His truth to those who seek with 
open eyes and hearts."

   [Open Windows, May 23, 1994.]
!TOPICS
EYES, SPIRITUAL
TRUTH
VISION
DISCERNMENT
