!TITLE
WHAT HUDSON TAYLOR "SAW" IN 1855
!WORDS
 The famed missionary to China Hudson Taylor, who founded the China 
Inland Mission, which was the first truly interdenominational foreign 
mission organization, was on furlough in England in 1855. One time 
when he was preaching, he suddenly stopped, closed his eyes, and 
didn't say anything for several moments.

   Finally, he spoke:  "I have seen a vision.  I saw in this vision a 
great war that encompasses the whole world.  I saw this war recess 
and then start again, actually being two wars. After this I saw much 
unrest and revolts that will affect many nations.  I saw in some 
places spiritual awakenings.  In Russia, I saw there will come a 
general all-encompassing, national spiritual awakening so great theat 
there could never be another like it.  I saw the awakening spread to 
many European countries.  Then I saw an all-out awakening, followed 
by the coming of Christ."

   [Intercessors for America Newsletter, Jul/Aug 1994.  Page 3.]
!TOPICS
REVIVAL
AWAKENING, SPIRITUAL
SECOND COMING, CHRIST'S
FUTURE, PREDICTING THE
PROPHECY
TAYLOR, HUDSON
