!TITLE
PEOPLE MATTER TO GOD
!WORDS
 Bill Hybels writes:  "The Anthropic Principle, which is very 
prevalent in the world of secular science and philosophy, didn't 
originate with Christian scholars.  Simply stated, the Anthropic 
Principle implies that when we look at the world around us, it would 
seem that the universe was somehow designed to support and nourish 
human life.

    "For example, if the ratio of carbon to oxygen had been slightly 
different than it is, none of us would have been here to breathe the 
air. Change the title of the earth's axis slightly in one direction, 
and we would freeze.  Change it the other direction, and we'd burn 
up.  The lesson we can draw from the Anthropic Principle is this: 
Someone must have gone to a lot of effort to make things just right 
so that you and I could be here to enjoy life.  We must really matter 
to God!

    "In the world of business, there's been a radical transformation 
during the last few years. Cutting-edge management experts have been 
talking about these developments in grandiose terms.  Tom Peters 
refers to a 'customer revolution,' and Ken Blanchard talks about the 
'upside-down pyramid.'
"It's time to turn over the corporate pyramid, these experts say, and 
get back to serving the person 'at the top'--and that's the customer, 
NOT the boss.

    "So if the lesson from science is that people matter to God, then 
the lesson from business is they'd better matter to US, too."

   [Becoming a Contagious Christian by Bill Hybels and Mark 
Mittelberg.  Zondervan, 1994.]
!TOPICS
LOVE FOR OTHERS
LOVE, GOD'S
EVANGELISM, PERSONAL
CARING
