!TITLE
OUR CARING CREATOR
!WORDS
 The Milky Way contains 100 billion stars--and that is just one small 
part of the vast heavens of which our planet is but a tiny speck.  
Considering the utter insignificance of our earth, it is hard to 
believe that the Creator of the cosmos cares about what happens to 
the human family that has been cynically described as a 
semi-invisible rash on the skin of a submicroscopic planet in a 
second-rate solar system.

   The astonishing truth is God does care.
