!TITLE
MERE CHILDREN
!WORDS
 A number of years ago, a girls' boarding school in India had some 
1,500 students, most of them Hindus.  One day some of the Christian 
students came to a missionary lady and asked her the meaning of Luke 
12:49: "I have come to bring fire on the earth, and how I wish it 
were already kindled!"  She gave them a rather vague answer because 
she was not sure herself, but they were determined to know.  They 
wanted that "fire" and began to pray for it.  The result of their 
prayers was a moving of the Holy Spirit that was very much like 
Pentecost.

   In the energy of the Spirit, they went to see another missionary 
who was staying nearby.  They asked him if they could stay in his 
town and pray for his work.  The missionary gave them permission to 
stay and pray in his barn.  Later as he sat down to eat dinner, an 
Indian pastor knocked on his door. It wasn't long before the pastor 
was weeping and confessing sins the Holy Spirit had convicted him 
of.  Soon another Christian came, and then another, and another, all 
confessing their sins and repenting.  What followed was an amazing 
time of backsliders being renewed and unbelievers being converted out 
of paganism--all because a handful of children started praying!
   [The Kneeling Christian.  Zondervan, 1971.]
