!TITLE
IF THE SHOE FITS
!WORDS
 Greg Laurie relates a practical joke "played many years ago by Sir 
Arthur Conan Doyle, author of the Sherlock Holmes stories.  One day 
Doyle, as a joke, jotted off a note to 12 of his friends. On this 
note he simply wrote these words:  `Flee at once.  All is discovered.'

    "Within 24 hours all 12 of his friends had left the country!"  
Laurie concludes, "That's a guilty conscience for you!"

   [Life. Any Questions? by Greg Laurie.  Word Publishing, 1995.  
Page 122.]
