!TITLE
WORRY IS A THIEF
!WORDS
 Pastor Bryan Fink tells how researchers at a state university in 
Ithaca, New York, performed a rather strange experiment a few years 
ago.  They administered electric shocks to a bunch of sheep. They 
were trying to ascertain just how much a sheep could tolerate.  The 
researchers found that after a certain period of time the sheep began 
to anticipate the next shock treatment.  By the time the study was 
nearly done, some of the sheep had become so anxious and worried 
about the next electrical shock that they could not function 
normally.  The sheep were, in fact, suffering from what is called 
among humans a "nervous breakdown."

   If we, like those sheep, get so concerned about what could happen 
to us, we will become immobilized and deprived of our freedom.  Worry 
can rob you of the peace of God.

   [Youthworker Update, Sep 1996.  Page 12.]
