!TITLE
LIFE'S NOT FAIR
!WORDS
 There's a fairy tale about a woman who had two daughters.  One was 
kind and considerate, but the other was mean and disagreeable.  The 
mother, however, showed favoritism to the unpleasant daughter and 
neglected the obedient girl.
   One day she sent the good daughter to the village well to draw 
water.  While there, she met and poor elderly woman who asked for a 
drink.  The girl spoke kind words to her and cheerfully gave her a 
drink.  The old woman, who was really a fairy in disguise, was so 
blessed by the girl's sweet attitude that she rewarded her.
    "Every word you speak will turn into a jewel or a flower as it 
falls from your mouth," she told the girl.  Arriving home, the young 
lady was berated for having taken so long at the well. When she 
started to explain what had happened, two pearls, three roses, and a 
diamond came out of her mouth.
   The mother was incredulous but could hardly deny the truth of her 
daughter's story, given the number of gems and blossoms that kept 
dropping from her lips.  Immediately, she called the other daughter 
and told her to go draw water at the well, hoping that she might be 
given the same gift.  The sister hated chores and grumbled and griped 
all the way to the well.
   The fairy was still there, but now she wore the disguise of a 
beautiful wealthy woman.  Again she asked for a drink.  But this girl 
was not at all like her sister.  She rudely and proudly refused to 
give the lady a drink.  She got a reward, but it was that every time 
she spoke toads and snakes came out of her mouth!
   We like stories fo this type because justice is done.  It's only 
fair that the good are blessed and the wicked punished.  Real life, 
however, is seldom like that.  Our everyday existence is shadowed by 
unfairness--the unfairness of disease, broken relationships, 
financial reverses, unequal work loads.
   [Hope Again by Charles Swindoll.  Word Publishing, 1996.  Pages 
133-134.]
!TOPICS
FAIRNESS
JUSTICE
REWARDS
WORDS
