!TITLE
HOTHOUSE TREES
!WORDS
 It is said that when large trees from southern Europe were first 
introduced into England, gardeners made the mistake of thinking they 
needed to be kept warm.  They put them in hothouses, but for some 
reason their leaves drooped and began to wither.  Unable to revive 
them, the gardeners gave up and threw the trees out.  Outside, 
exposed to the extremes of the climate, the little trees took root 
and began to grow.

   Something like this happens to us as Christians.  We may feel 
abandoned and cast out because of the cold, inhospitable 
circumstances in which we find ourselves, but it is exactly these 
kinds of experiences that the Lord uses to produce spiritual growth 
in us.  Unlike the ignorant gardeners, He knows exactly what kind of 
soil and climate will grow our faith and knowledge of Him.
   [Bible Truth Illustrated by Donald Grey Barnhouse.  Fleming H. 
Revell, 1979.  Page 150.]
!TOPICS
