!TITLE
PEACE OF MIND
!WORDS
 Dan Montgomery tells the following story about a guy named Billy, a 
self-made man who owned a ranch out west which he used for summer 
camps.  One day Dan noticed a bad rash on Billy's arms and he asked 
him about it.  "Oh, that's just something I get whenever I'm all 
knotted up inside."

   Dan asked what he was so worried about.  Billy explained that 100 
people were coming for summer camp the following week.  Because of 
heavy rains that spring, the grass on the campground was knee high.  
He couldn't get it mowed because his power mower had quit working and 
his tractor was broken down and wouldn't be fixed for two weeks.  He 
was at wit's end about it.

   Dan suggested he ask God to help him figure out something.  "I 
hadn't thought about that," said Billy.  "I've always handled 
everything on my own."

    "Well, it can't hurt to ask," Dan said. "Maybe God can help you 
out."

   The next week when Dan ran into Billy in town, he asked the 
rancher how things were going.  Billy said, "Great!  The day after I 
talked to you, I was sitting up there looking at that huge field of 
grass, and I said, `OK, God, if You exist, please help me out.'"

   A few minutes later, Billy had gotten the idea to go over to his 
neighbor's place and see if he wanted to graze any horses in that 
pasture.  Come to find out, the neighbor had been looking for a place 
to graze six of his horses.  Billy's acre of high grass was the 
perfect solution--to both their problems.

    "He brought the horses over that afternoon," said Billy, "and by 
the time camp started yesterday, that field looked like it had been 
mowed and trimmed by professionals!"

    "Wonderful," Dan exclaimed and commented that Billy's arm rash 
seemed to have cleared up.
    "Yeah," said Billy rubbing the smooth skin on his tanned arms.  
"I finally got some peace of mind."

   [Pursuit, Vol 70, No 2, 1996.  Pages 10-11.]
