!TITLE
FAITHFUL WITNESS
!WORDS
 Eastman Curtis tells about a high school student in Mississippi 
named Sherry, who  began trying to witness for Christ.  She carried 
her Bible to school and would read a chapter at lunch.  She prayed 
before she ate.  She often wore T-shirts with a Christian message on 
them.

   At first some of the guys made fun of her, but she just kept doing 
these things.  One day about three weeks later, she was in the 
library and the quarterback of the football team walked by. Suddenly, 
he stopped and turned around.

   He said, "I'm going to hell, aren't I?"  Then she noticed he had 
tears rolling down his cheeks. Very gently Sherry answered his 
question:  "If you don't know the Lord Jesus Christ, you are."
    "How can I get what you've got?" he asked.  "I know I need it."

   Sherry briefly shared the gospel with him, and they prayed 
together right there in the library. By the end of the school year, 
that quarterback had influenced a number of other guys on the team to 
accept Christ...all because of one girl's faithfulness.

   [Charisma, Oct 1996.  Page 68.]
