!TITLE
WHEN YOUR WORLD FALLS APART
!WORDS
 Christian counselor Sonny Acho remembers a sci-fi movie from the 
1960s.  The plot went something like this:  Some scientists had the 
idea of tapping the geothermal energy at the earth's core so they 
punched a hole in the earth's crust.  As a result superheated nickel 
poured out and began to eat away the planet.

   Eventually, the earth split in two.  Despite heroic scientific and 
technological efforts to avoid a catastrophe, a big chunk of the 
planet came loose and drifted off into space.

   Acho makes this application:  "Whatever is eating away at your 
world God dearly wants to fix. However, if the crack is to be stopped 
before your whole world falls apart, then God alone has to do it.  
The more you try in your own strength, the more you will fail; and 
the more you fail, the more you will hurt."

   [Picking Up the Pieces by O. Sonny Acho. Crossway Books, 1996.]
