!TITLE
WHEN THE WHEAT GROWS HIGHER
!WORDS
 An American went to England in the springtime. Looking out the 
airplane window as they flew over the English countryside, he was 
intrigued by the geometric designs formed by the intricate network of 
stone fences.

   He went back a few months later, but this time when he looked out 
the window the fences were all gone.  He asked the stewardess what 
had happened to all the fences.  She replied, "Oh, sir, it's harvest 
time now.  The wheat has grown up higher than the fences, so you 
can't see them."

   Pastor John Kilpatrick says it's harvest time in the Christian 
church today.  In this time of revival, we shouldn't be looking for 
the fences. We should be focusing on the wheat--the harvest.
!TOPICS
