!TITLE
WHEN GOD HIDES HIS FACE
!WORDS
When he was a little boy in Birmingham, Eddie Smith loved to go 
downtown to Woolworth's department store with his grandmother.  
Almost as soon as they entered the store, he would pull his little 
hand out of hers and make a beeline for the toy department.

   One day when he did that he was in for a big shock.  He got to the 
toy aisle and found that it had been moved.  Suddenly feeling very 
lost, toys were the last thing on his mind.  He was desperate to find 
his grandmother.  Pretty soon he was crying as he went from aisle to 
aisle looking for her.

   Years later Grandmother confessed that she decided to teach him a 
lesson.  So as little Eddie would come along looking for her, she 
would quietly hide behind a display until he went by. Finally, she 
let him see her, and he came running and threw his arms around her.

   She didn't hide from him out of a lack of love, He was precious to 
her, but she hid from him to teach him the importance of walking with 
her.

   Sometimes God may pull away from us for a time, but it isn't 
because He doesn't love us.
   [Beyond the Veil by Alice Smith.  SpiriTruth Publishing, 1996.  
Pages 156-157.]
!TOPICS
