!TITLE
WHAT A WASTE!
!WORDS
Jalil was a secondary schoolteacher in Malaysia, but the real joy of 
his life was coaching.  He loved coaching the younger teenagers.  In 
that country, coaches are highly respected.  Jalil considered it an 
honor to serve as coach of the soccer team from his school.
   But Jalil will never coach again.  One night while his team was a 
national soccer tournament, Jalil violated his personal standards and 
spent one night with a prostitute.  Apprehended by local authorities, 
Jalil faced disciplinary action by the Malaysian Soccer Association.  
Although Jalil was repentant and apologized publicly for his 
behavior, the verdict from the association was "banned from coaching 
for life."  In part the ruling read, "We cannot condone such 
behavior, especially on the part of one who is supposed to set a good 
example for young people."
   Jalil was devastated.  What a waste!  No more soccer, no more 
coaching.  Even though he begged for forgiveness, it was not granted 
because of his position.  As followers of Christ, we are likewise 
expected to live in purity.  If we violate God's standards, we will 
face devastating consequences.
   [Campus Journal, Dec 15, 1995.
