!TITLE
CONSCIENCE-STRICKEN
!WORDS
Back in 1977 Julian Imperial broke into the home of Mary Stein, a 
73-year-old California woman.  He and a accomplice bludgeoned her to 
death with a piece of wood.  The helpless woman's dying words were: 
"Oh, Lord, I'm coming home."

   Those simple words that Mary Stein whispered as she went out into 
eternity haunted Julian Imperial.  A year after the murder, he came 
to faith in Christ.  His sense of guilt and responsibility 
intensified over the years. Seventeen years later, even though the 
police were no longer considering him a suspect in the unsolved case, 
Julian felt impelled to tell the truth about what he had done.  His 
conscience would not leave him in peace, so he turned himself in to 
the police and confessed his involvement in the crime.

   Although he is in prison today, Julian now enjoys an inner freedom 
he would never have known had he not listened to his conscience.

   [World, May 17, 1997.  Page 25.]
