!TITLE
THE WILL TO LIVE
!WORDS
Robert A. Chesebrough was a chemist in Brooklyn. When he invented 
Vaseline, he thought he had discovered the secret of a long life.  He 
told people to swallow one teaspoon of Vaseline every day.  He lived 
to be 96, but one day in 1933, he died-- probably choked.
   We all have a God-given desire to live.  Even the most ignorant 
human knows that life is better than death.  Immortality, or at least 
longevity, is what the human heart longs for.  But the Bible teaches 
that we are all under the fear of death until we come to the Savior.
   [Everyday Evangelism by Ray Comfort. Huntington House.]
