!TITLE
STICKING IT OUT
!WORDS
Military life isn't for everybody.  It's tough. Not everyone can meet 
the demands.  Official Army estimates say that of the almost 88,000 
soldiers who enlisted in 1997, some 33,000 will no longer be in the 
service in three years.  For a variety of reasons (mental or physical 
problems, poor performance, misconduct), one out of three recruits 
doesn't last three years.

   The same thing happens at colleges and universities.  During that 
freshman year, money problems and bad grades force many students to 
call it quits.

   Often people who seem quite interested in Christianity don't last 
very long either.  In Jesus' parable of the soils, three of the four 
types of people didn't make it as His followers.

   [Campus Journal, Sep 2, 1997.]
