!TITLE
A SLOW STARTER WHO DIDN'T QUIT
!WORDS
Barry Sanders, the former outstanding running back of the Detroit 
Lions, is a Christian and an excellent example of perseverance. In 
high school, he didn't start for his football team until midway 
through his senior year. At Oklahoma State University, he didn't 
start until his junior year. Many professional scouts thought he 
would be too small and not be able to handle the pounding of 
professional football, but they too have been proven wrong.
