!TITLE
THE WORK OF GOD DISPLAYED
!WORDS
On November 29, 1992 Dennis Byrd lined up on the New York Jets 
defensive line against the Kansas City Chiefs. With the snap of the 
ball, Dennis pursued the quarterback. As he reached out toward his 
opponent, he collided headfirst with his teammate and crashed to the 
ground. He shattered a vertebrae in his neck and was paralyzed. 
Everyone was motionless as he was carted from the playing field to a 
waiting ambulance. Doctors weren't sure Dennis would live, and if he 
did, if he would ever walk again. As he lay motionless in his 
hospital bed, the 6-5, 270 pound giant cried in the middle of the 
night. He "knew that through perseverance God would make this a 
blessing, even if it was just for one person." The Lord honored 
Dennis' faith in Him. Within two months of his accident, he began to 
walk again. Everyone marveled at how the Lord had worked in his life. 
He said, "How could I possibly ask "why me?" That's the miracle. 
That's the magic. It's knowing that all life is a blessing, that the 
Lord is with us, even when we falter, He is with us even if we fail, 
He is with us when we break."
!TOPICS
MIRACLES
HEALS, GOD
HEALING
LAME
RESTORATION
WALKING
