!TITLE
AN OPEN LINE
!WORDS
Nowadays we communicate with other people around the globe via 
satellites, fiber optics, and the internet, but over a century ago a 
man named Cyrus Field had a very radical idea.  He envisioned laying 
a cable across the Atlantic Ocean between the United States and 
Europe so that telegraph messages could be sent back and forth.  Such 
an undertaking would be difficult and expensive, but Field managed to 
convince both the American and British governments to finance the 
project.

   Once the cable had been manufactured, they began the arduous task 
of laying it across miles and miles of the ocean floor.  Only 360 
miles out, the cable broke, and they had to start over. After a 
year-long delay, the process began again. They finally succeeded in 
getting the cable all the way across, but the system had been 
operational only a short time when the cable broke once more.

   Field was hardly in a position to try again. His funds were 
depleted.  A fire had destroyed his business office.  Yet he 
persevered.  After seven long years of trying to raise the capital 
for another attempt, he finally had enough.  This time they had laid 
1,200 miles of cable when it snapped again.  Did Field take this as a 
sign that he should quit?  No!  A fourth cable was manufactured and 
after more years and many more dollars was put into operation.

   Just as Mr. Field provided a way of communication between Europe 
and America, God has made a way of communication between heaven and 
earth...through His Son.  It was an extremely costly project.  Jesus 
had to come to earth and die for the sins of mankind, but He didn't 
have to try and fail and try again.  He did everything right the 
first time.

   [Stories to Tell in Children's Church by Velma Kiefer.  Baker, 
1966.  Pages 69-70.]
!TOPICS
PERSEVERANCE
COMMUNICATION WITH GOD
JESUS CHRIST
CROSS, CHRIST'S
PERSISTENCE
RECONCILIATION WITH GOD
