!TITLE
BEING LED THE WRONG WAY
!WORDS
Clayton Lonetree was born in Chicago in 1961. His family was very 
patriotic with several of his ancestors having served in the Civil 
War and in both world wars. Two of his uncles fought with distinction 
in Vietnam, and a third uncle, who fought in the Korean War, was 
awarded posthumously the Medal of Honor for heroism. Clayton grew up 
wanting to follow in their footsteps. His mother described him as "a 
good, obedient son, a law-abiding Baptist who knew the Bible and who 
never got so much as a traffic ticket." 

After high school, he joined the U.S. Marine Corps and rose to the 
rank of sergeant. In 1985 he was assigned to the elite detail that 
guards the U.S. Embassy in Moscow. In November 1985, Lonetree began a 
love affair with a beautiful Russian secretary who worked at the 
embassy. She introduced him to her "uncle" who was a KGB agent and 
slowly Lonetree was seduced into spying against his country. He 
turned over several classified documents to the KGB. Realizing his 
terrible actions, he alerted American authorities. In August 1987, he 
was convicted of espionage and sentenced to thirty years in prison. 
Evil is never far away. It crouches near us waiting to take 
advantage. Our only defense is to trust in the grace of God.
!TOPICS
ASTRAY
PRIDE
SEX, LURE OF
BETRAYAL
TEMPTATION
ESPIONAGE
!SCRIPTURES
ROMANS 7:21
PSALMS 143:10
ROMANS 8:14
